            <h2>Further collaboration</h2>

            <p>After the success of the partnership of photographer, poet and scientist, Crawford wondered whether he could replicate the project for other artists. Partnering up three students who were undertaking a MLitt in Creative Writing &mdash; Helen Nicholson, Amanda Merritt and Tristram Fane Saunders &mdash; with a scientist and local photographer, each wrote a poem inspired by the research done in St Andrews. </p>

            <p><em>Summer</em>, a poem by MLitt student Amanda Merritt, winds together musings on light and nature with that of the physical body; a brief, touching poem, accompanied by a photo by Kim Bennett.  </p>

